in lieu of stock options. The Company generally grants restricted stock units that have a service condition only or have both a service and
performance condition. Each restricted stock unit is not considered issued and outstanding and does not have voting rights until it is
converted into one share of the Company's common stock upon vesting. Restricted stock unit activity is summarized as follows:
