Federal and state tax laws, including California tax laws, impose substantial restrictions on the utilization of NOL and credit
carryforwards in the event of an "ownership change" for tax purposes, as defined in Section 382 of the Internal Revenue Code. An
ownership change occurred during fiscal year 2002, which resulted in an annual limitation of approximately $0.8 million for NOL
carryforwards generated prior to 2003.
